#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:4
msgid "Numark Mixtrack (Pro) 3"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:6
msgid ""
"`Manufacturer’s product page <https://www.numark.com/product/mixtrack-"
"pro-3>`__"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:7
msgid ""
"`Manufacturer's User Manual "
"<https://www.numark.com/images/product_downloads/MixtrackPro3-UserGuide-v1.1.pdf>`__"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:8
msgid ""
"`Forum thread <https://mixxx.discourse.group/t/mixtrack-pro-3/15165>`__"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:10
msgid ""
"The Numark Mixtrack 3 and Numark Mixtrack Pro 3 are the same controller "
"except that the Pro version has an integrated 4 channel output sound card "
"and costs $50 more. If you use the non-Pro version, you would need a "
":ref:`splitter cable <hardware-splitter-cables>` or :ref:`separate audio "
"interface <hardware-audio-interfaces>` to be able to preview tracks in "
"headphones."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:17
msgid ""
"The microphone input on the Pro version is not available to the computer "
"through the controller’s sound card. It is mixed with the main output in "
"hardware, so this controller’s sound card is not suitable for broadcasting "
"or recording the inputs. If you want to use the controller for broadcasting "
"or recording, getting the non-Pro version with a separate :ref:`audio "
"interface <hardware-audio-interfaces>` with a microphone input is suggested."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:29
msgid "Mapping Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:38
msgid "Numark Mixtrack (Pro) 3 (schematic view)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:42
msgid "1. Browser Knob"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:45
msgid ""
"Rotate this knob to cycle through tracks in main library window. Press the "
"Knob to expand library view."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:47
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`SHIFT` **+ Turn:** allows selecting Play Lists and side navigation"
" bar items."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:48
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`SHIFT` **+ Push:** opens / closes selected side navigation bar "
"item."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:50
msgid ""
"**Configurable option:** In Focus mode the Browse encoder affects the "
"library widget which currently has keyboard focus. This requires the Mixxx "
"window to have focus and allows to control the searchbar, too. In Classic "
"mode the Browse encoder can select items in the sidebar and tracks table "
"only, but independent of keyboard focus."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:58
msgid "2. Master Gain"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:60
msgid "Adjusts the main volume in the software."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:63
msgid ""
"**Note**: This control does not affect the microphone volume which is summed"
" with the final output of the main gain to the main output. Use the Mic Gain"
" knob to control the microphone volume."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:66
msgid "3. Cue Mix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:68
msgid ""
"Adjusts the software’s audio output to the headphones, mixing between the "
"cue (PFL) output and the main mix output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:72
msgid "4. Cue Gain"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:74
msgid "Adjusts the volume for headphone cueing in the software."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:77
msgid "5. Load"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:80
msgid ""
"Press one of these buttons while a track is selected in the library window "
"to assign it to Deck 1 and 2, respectively, in the software."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:86
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`SHIFT` + :hwlabel:`LOAD`: Activates Fader Start mode for the "
"corresponding (PFL Button is then blinking). Fader start guide: In fader "
"start mode, not only you can press the play/pause button to play/pause the "
"track, but if you move up the level fader (the volume fader if you prefer) "
"of the deck, the track will be played and if you close it to zero, the track"
" will be paused."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:88
msgid ""
"**Configurable option:** If the smartPFL option is set to true, the Cue/PFL "
"button is automatically activated on the deck being loaded and deactivated "
"on the other deck."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:93
msgid "6. High EQ Knobs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:95
msgid "Adjust High frequencies of the deck"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:96
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`SHIFT` + :hwlabel:`HIGH`: Adjust parameter 1 of the currently "
"focused effect on this deck."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:99
msgid "7. Mid EQ Knobs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:101
msgid "Adjust Mid frequencies of the deck"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:102
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`SHIFT` + :hwlabel:`MID`: Adjust parameter 2 of the currently "
"focused effect on this deck."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:105
msgid "8 Low EQ Knobs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:107
msgid "Adjust Low frequencies of the deck"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:108
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`SHIFT` + :hwlabel:`LOW`: Adjust parameter 3 of the currently "
"focused effect on this deck."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:111
msgid "9. Filter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:115
msgid ""
"Adjusts the amount of the filter effect. Turning the knob left controls the "
"low pass filter; turning it right controls the high pass filter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:116
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`SHIFT` + :hwlabel:`FILTER`: Adjust parameter 4 of the currently "
"focused effect on this deck."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:117
msgid "If effect is unfocused then;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:118
msgid ":hwlabel:`SHIFT` + :hwlabel:`FILTER` Adjust the gain of the deck."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:120
msgid ""
"**Configurable option:** Adjust FX parameter 4 (default) or deck gain when "
"unfocused."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:124
msgid "10. Cue/PFL/Headphones"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:126
msgid "Sends pre-fader audio to the headphone output"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:127
msgid ":hwlabel:`SHIFT` + :hwlabel:`CUE/PFL`: Toggle quantize mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:130
msgid "11. Volume fader"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:132
msgid "Adjusts the volume of the deck"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:135
msgid "12. Crossfader"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:137
msgid "Controls the blend between the two decks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:140
msgid "13-14. Pitch Bend Down/Up"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:142
msgid "Press and hold to momentarily reduce the speed of the track."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:143
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`SHIFT` + **PITCH BEND** :hwlabel:`-`/:hwlabel:`+`: Jump 1 beat "
"backward/forward"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:144
msgid "- If loop is activated, move loop by beatjump amount instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:147
msgid "15. Pitch Fader"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:149
msgid ""
"Adjust the speed of the music (activate keylock to adjust tempo without "
"affecting pitch). Note that moving the fader down *increases* speed, as "
"marked by the “+” at the bottom of the fader on the controller. This can be "
"reversed in Mixxx’s preferences under Interface > Speed slider direction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:156
msgid "16. Touch Strip"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:160
msgid ""
"Use the Touch Strip to adjust the deck’s Effect Unit Superknob. If Effects "
"are assigned to Instant FX , they will be enabled instantly on touch, and "
"disabled on finger lift."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:161
msgid ":hwlabel:`SHIFT` + **Touch Strip**: search through a track’s timeline"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:164
msgid "17. Beats Multiplier"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:166
msgid "Adjusts the Dry/Wet mix of the deck’s Effect Unit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:168
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`TAP` + :hwlabel:`BEATS`: Moves the beat grid left (turn "
"counterclockwise) or right (turn clockwise)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:169
msgid ":hwlabel:`SHIFT` + :hwlabel:`BEATS`: Adjust beatjump amount"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:171
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`PADMODE` + :hwlabel:`BEATS`: Adjust Sampler Volume. Left beat knob"
" will adjust Samplers 1-4; Right knob will adjust Samplers 5-8"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:174
msgid "18. FX 1 On/Off"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:176
msgid "Turns FX1 on and off"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:177
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`SHIFT` + :hwlabel:`FX1`: Select from the list of available effects"
" for the respective effect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:179
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`PADMODE` + :hwlabel:`FX1`: Assign / unassign FX 1 to Instant FX. "
"When assigned to Instant FX, the FX is instantly activated by touching the "
"Strip and stopped when finger is lifted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:180
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`TAP` + :hwlabel:`FX1`: Focus this effect to allow adjusting its "
"metaknob with the touch strip."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:183
msgid "19. FX 2 On/Off"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:185
msgid "Turns FX2 on and off"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:186
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`SHIFT` + :hwlabel:`FX2`: Select from the list of available effects"
" for the respective effect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:188
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`PADMODE` + :hwlabel:`FX2`: Assign / unassign FX 1 to Instant FX. "
"When assigned to Instant FX, the FX is instantly activated by touching the "
"Strip and stopped when finger is lifted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:189
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`TAP` + :hwlabel:`FX2`: Focus this effect to allow adjusting its "
"metaknob with the touch strip."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:192
msgid "20. FX 3 On/Off"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:194
msgid "Turns FX3 on and off"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:195
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`SHIFT` + :hwlabel:`FX3`: Select from the list of available effects"
" for the respective effect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:197
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`PADMODE` + :hwlabel:`FX3`: Assign / unassign FX 1 to Instant FX. "
"When assigned to Instant FX, the FX is instantly activated by touching the "
"Strip and stopped when finger is lifted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:198
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`TAP` + :hwlabel:`FX3`: Focus this effect to allow adjusting its "
"metaknob with the touch strip."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:201
msgid "21. Tap BPM"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:205
msgid ""
"Press this 8 or more times on beat to manually enter a new BPM. The software"
" will ignore the track’s BPM and follow your manually entered tempo."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:208
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`SHIFT` + :hwlabel:`TAP`: Toggles deck between deck 1-3 (left side)"
" or deck 2-4 (right side). TAP LED will be RED when deck 3 is active (Left "
"Tap) or deck 4 is active (Right Tap)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:209
msgid ":hwlabel:`TAP` + :hwlabel:`HOTCUE 1`: Activates Brake effect"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:210
msgid ":hwlabel:`TAP` + :hwlabel:`HOTCUE 2`: Activates Spinback effect"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:213
msgid "22. Wheel button"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:216
msgid ""
"Activate this button to use the platter/jog wheel to grab and move the "
"audio, scratching the track like a vinyl record."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:217
msgid ":hwlabel:`SHIFT` + :hwlabel:`WHEEL`: Toggle slip mode on/off"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:219
msgid ""
"**Configurable option**: The jog wheel button flashes near the end of a "
"track by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:222
msgid "23. Platter/Jog Wheel"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:227
msgid ""
"**Touch side:** Pitch bend (nudging) if track is playing (Wheel On (always) "
"& Wheel Off - if `PitchBendOnWheelOff <#configuration-options>`__ "
"configuration option is true) and / track positioning (Wheel On)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:228
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`WHEEL` **On** + **Touch platter**: scratching: touch the platter "
"and move it"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:230
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`WHEEL` **Off** + **Touch platter**: If track is not playing, "
"allows positioning the track"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:231
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`SHIFT` + :hwlabel:`WHEEL` **Off** + **Touch platter**: fast seek "
"through track"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:236
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`SHIFT` + :hwlabel:`WHEEL` **On** + **Touch platter**: iCut mode: "
"simulates a scratch routine with the jog wheel. When the jog wheel is turned"
" back, the crossfader closes; when the jog wheel is turned forward the "
"crossfader will open. As a visual reference, TAP LED and Wheel button LED "
"will be ON."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:238
msgid ""
"**Configurable Options:** The iCutEnabled and fastSeekEnabled options can be"
" used to turn off iCut and fast seeking. These options may be helpful to "
"avoid accidentally using these features when touching the platter with shift"
" lock on. The PitchBendOnWheelOff option allows pitch bending using the jog "
"wheel even when the scratch mode is disabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:245
msgid "24. Shift"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:248
msgid ""
"Allows multiple control commands to be triggered when pressed first along "
"with other buttons"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:251
msgid "25. Pad Mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:253
msgid ""
"This is used to change the operation mode of the `top 4 performance pads "
"<#29.-Performance-Pads>`__. Pressing this button will light the pad "
"indicating the currently active mode (Manual Loop, Auto Loop or Sampler)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:259
msgid "26. Sync"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:261
msgid "Enables BPM syncing between decks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:263
msgid ""
"**Short Press:** Press once to synchronize the tempo (BPM) to that of to "
"that of the other track"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:266
msgid ""
"**Double Press:** press twice QUICKLY to play the track immediately "
"synchronized to the tempo (BPM) and to the phase of the other track, if the "
"track was paused"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:272
msgid ""
"**Long Press** (Sync Lock): Hold for at least half of a second to enable "
"sync lock for this deck. Decks with sync locked will all play at the same "
"tempo, and decks that also have quantize enabled will always have their "
"beats lined up. If the Sync Lock was previously activated, it just "
"deactivates it regardless of the Short press/Double Press"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:273
msgid ":hwlabel:`SHIFT` + :hwlabel:`SYNC`: Toggle Key Lock"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:275
msgid ""
"**Configuration Options:** The noPlayOnSyncDoublePress option can be used to"
" turn off Play on Sync Double Press."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:279
msgid "27. Cue (Transport Control)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:281
msgid ""
"Behavior depends on the :ref:`cue mode <interface-cue-modes>` set in the "
"Mixxx preferences."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:282
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`SHIFT` + :hwlabel:`CUE`: Return the play head to the start of the "
"track."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:285
msgid "28. Play/Pause"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:288
msgid ""
"Starts and suspends playback. If no track is loaded, loads the selected "
"track (if any) and play."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:291
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`SHIFT` + :hwlabel:`PLAY/PAUSE`: Stutter the track from the last "
"set cue point. If a cue point has not been set, the play head will return to"
" the start of the track."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:294
msgid "29. Performance Pads"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:296
msgid ""
"The top row of pads is for controlling loops and samples. To select a mode, "
"hold down the Pad Mode button and press one of the upper pads. An LED under "
"the pad section indicates the currently selected mode. See the subsections "
"below for details about each mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:304
msgid ""
"The bottom row of pads is used to trigger hotcue points. If a hotcue point "
"has not already been set for the loaded track, this control will mark the "
"hotcue point. If a hotcue point has already been set, this control will jump"
" to it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:305
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`SHIFT` + :hwlabel:`HOTCUE`: Deletes the assigned hotcue point"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:308
msgid "Manual Loop Mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:310
msgid ""
"Hold :hwlabel:`PADMODE` and press the pad marked Manual Loop (silkscreened "
"above the pad) to assign the lower 4 pads to the functions listed below:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:313
msgid ""
"**Loop In** – Sets the beginning of a loop: When assigned, the Pad LED will "
"light blue"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:315
msgid ""
"**Loop Out** – Sets the end point for the loop: When assigned, the Pad LED "
"will light blue"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:317
msgid ""
"**On/Off** – (De)activate the loop. If a loop has not been set, this button "
"will have no effect.: When assigned, the Pad LED will light blue"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:320
msgid ""
"**Loop x1/2** – Halve the length of the loop. Press :hwlabel:`SHIFT` + "
"**Loop x1/2** to double the length of the loop. x1/2 button is disabled "
"unless the corresponding deck is set to be quantized"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:326
msgid "Auto Loop Mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:330
msgid ""
"Hold Pad Mode and press the pad marked Autoloop to assign the lower 4 pads "
"to the functions listed below: When assigned, the respective Pad LED will "
"blink Yellow"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:332
msgid "**Auto 1** – Sets and starts playback of a 2-beat autoloop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:333
msgid "**Auto 2** – Sets and starts playback of a 4-beat autoloop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:334
msgid "**Auto 3** – Sets and starts playback of a 8-beat autoloop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:335
msgid "**Auto 4** – Sets and starts playback of a 16-beat autoloop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:336
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`SHIFT` **+ Auto 1** – Sets and starts playback of a 1/8-beat "
"autoloop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:337
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`SHIFT` **+ Auto 2** – Sets and starts playback of a 1/4-beat "
"autoloop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:338
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`SHIFT` **+ Auto 3** – Sets and starts playback of a 1/2-beat "
"autoloop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:339
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`SHIFT` **+ Auto 4** – Sets and starts playback of a 1-beat "
"autoloop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_3.rst:341
msgid ""
